snippet: Researchers found that an increased risk of death in young adulthood was independent of sex, birth order, maternal age, parental education or marital status, and birth weight.
lead_paragraph: Researchers found that an increased risk of death in young adulthood was independent of sex, birth order, maternal age, parental education or marital status, and birth weight.

headline.main: Patterns: Risks for Preemies Resurface Years Later
headline.print_headline: Patterns: Dangers for Preemies Persist Years Later
headline.seo: Higher Risk of Death for Preemies Returns in Young Adulthood
